cs.DM, cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with a graph model that involves boxes in a metric space, which suggests that it could belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) category. The use of representative elements and the focus on the Euclidean line also suggest a possible connection to Computational Geometry (cs.CG). The combinatorial and intersection characterizations of the model suggest a connection to Data Structures (cs.DS) and Graph Theory (cs.GT). Finally, the study of particular cases and the construction of a graph family that separates them suggest a possible connection to Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
